    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - LIGHT SYSTEMS - DESCRIPTION - Trailer Work or
        Hook-Up
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Trailer Work or Hook-Up</title>
        <para>The work light circuit consists of a work light, a work light switch, and an indicator light located in
            the instrument cluster. The work light, located on the back of the sleeper, provides light for the operator
            when the trailer air and electrical lines are being connected or disconnected from the trailer.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
